    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear the exhaustion in your words, and I want to validate that when the foundation of your life is removed, the feeling of being at the bottom isn't just a metaphor—it is a terrifying, heavy reality. It makes perfect sense that you feel tired of searching for reasons to keep going when the ground beneath you has simply vanished.\n\nHowever, even in the deepest darkest hole, there are often small, invisible things still there that we can't see from the surface. Sometimes, when we are too focused on the \"zero,\" we miss the tiny, stubborn things that refuse to die with us.\n\nI know you might not feel like a \"climbing out\" is possible right now, but I also know that even the most despairing situations have a way of shifting if we just wait for the right moment. You are not alone in this darkness, and I am here to sit with you in the hole until you are ready to look for those small, unseen things again. Please, if you can, reach out to a crisis line or a trusted person who can offer support when you feel like the ground is truly gone. You matter, and your story hasn't ended yet, even if it feels like it has.",
